ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. How much of the living area in your home is cluttered with possessions? (Consider the amount of clutter in your kitchen, living room, dining room, hallways, bedroom, bathrooms, or other rooms).
Notes: 0= None; 1= A little; 2= A moderate amount; 3= Most/Much; 4= Almost All/Complete

ElementDescription: 2. How much control do you have over your urges to acquire possessions?
Notes: 0= None; 1= A little; 2= A moderate amount; 3= Most/Much; 4= Almost All/Complete

ElementDescription: 3. How much of your home does clutter prevent you from using?
Notes: 0= None; 1= A little; 2= A moderate amount; 3= Most/Much; 4= Almost All/Complete

ElementDescription: 4. How much control do you have over your urges to save possessions?
Notes: 0= None; 1= A little; 2= A moderate amount; 3= Most/Much; 4= Almost All/Complete

ElementDescription: 5. How much of your home is difficult to walk through because of clutter?
Notes: 0= None; 1= A little; 2= A moderate amount; 3= Most/Much; 4= Almost All/Complete

ElementDescription: 6. To what extent do you have difficulty throwing things away?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 7. How distressing do you find the task of throwing things away?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 8. To what extent do you have so many things that your room(s) are cluttered?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 9. How distressed or uncomfortable would you feel if you could not acquire something you wanted?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 10. How much does clutter in your home interfere with your social, work or everyday functioning? Think about things that you don't do because of clutter.
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 11. How strong is your urge to buy or acquire free things for which you have no immediate use?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 12. To what extent does clutter in your home cause you distress?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 13. How strong is your urge to save something you know you may never use?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 14. How upset or distressed do you feel about your acquiring habits?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 15. To what extent do you feel unable to control the clutter in your home?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 16. To what extent has your saving or compulsive buying resulted in financial difficulties for you?
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Considerable/Severe; 4= Extreme

ElementDescription: 17. How often do you avoid trying to discard possessions because it is too stressful or time consuming?
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Rarely; 2= Sometimes/Occasionally; 3= Frequently/Often; 4= Very Often

ElementDescription: 18. How often do you feel compelled to acquire something you see? e.g. when shopping or offered free things?
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Rarely; 2= Sometimes/Occasionally; 3= Frequently/Often; 4= Very Often

ElementDescription: 19. How often do you decide to keep things you do not need and have little space for?
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Rarely; 2= Sometimes/Occasionally; 3= Frequently/Often; 4= Very Often

ElementDescription: 20. How frequently does clutter in your home prevent you from inviting people to visit?
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Rarely; 2= Sometimes/Occassionally; 3= Frequently/Often; 4= Very Often

ElementDescription: 21. How often do you actually buy (or acquire for free) things for which you have no immediate use or need?
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Rarely; 2= Sometimes/Occasionally; 3= Frequently/Often; 4= Very Often

ElementDescription: 22. To what extent does the clutter in your home prevent you from using parts of your home for their intended purpose? For example, cooking, using furniture, washing dishes, cleaning etc...
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Rarely; 2= Sometimes/Occasionally; 3= Frequently/Often; 4= Very Often

ElementDescription: 23. How often are you unable to discard a possession you would like to get rid of?
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Rarely; 2= Sometimes/Occasionally; 3= Frequently/Often; 4= Very Often
